text: Donald William KempKEMP DONALD WILLIAM (21 July 1914 – 22 April 1973) was an Australian rules footballer who played with North Melbourne in the VFL. Kemp was North Melbourne's best and fairest winner in 1943 and when he retired in 1947 finished one game short of joining the 100 game club. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1914 births Category:1973 deaths Category:Australian rules footballers from Victoria (Australia) Category:North Melbourne Football Club players Category:Syd Barker Medal winners
